cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with computer vision algorithms and the importance of training datasets, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a gradient-based importance measure and analysis of training images also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The analysis of diversity in training examples could also place it in the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the mention of active learning on deep networks suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
